>>summary: Product

^^^^tspp_spec_start type:PLAIN_TEXT
<div style="font-size: inherit;">1. Product Information Display\r\nFR1: Product Details Display\r\n\r\nThe product page must prominently display the name of the product, its price in a clear and readable format, and the unique SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) identifier to facilitate inventory tracking and product identification.\r\nFR2: Product Image Quality and Display\r\n\r\nA high-resolution image of the product shall be presented, which users can view to assess the product's features. The image should be clear enough to allow users to make informed decisions based on the visual details of the product.\r\n2. Product Attributes Selection\r\nFR3: Attribute Selection Options\r\n\r\nUsers must be able to select product attributes, such as size and color, if applicable. These options should be presented in a user-friendly manner, allowing for easy selection.\r\nFR4: Size Selection Interface\r\n\r\nAll available sizes for a product shall be presented in a selectable format, perhaps as buttons or drop-down options, with the selected size being distinctly highlighted to avoid user confusion.\r\nFR5: Color Selection Interface\r\n\r\nThe product page shall display all available colors. Similar to size selection, the chosen color option should be clearly indicated to users.\r\n3. Quantity Selection\r\nFR6: Quantity Selection Feature\r\n\r\nThe product page shall include a feature for users to select the quantity they wish to purchase, with controls to increment or decrement the desired amount within the bounds of the available stock.\r\nFR7: Quantity Selection Default and Limitations\r\n\r\nThe default quantity set upon loading the product page shall be one (1). The system shall ensure that users can only select a quantity within the range of available stock to prevent orders that cannot be fulfilled.\r\n4. Add to Cart Functionality\r\nFR8: 'Add to Cart' Button Functionality\r\n\r\nAn \"Add to Cart\" button shall be available and prominently displayed on the product page. Upon selection of the desired attributes and quantity, clicking this button shall add the product to the user's shopping cart.\r\nFR9: User Feedback on Adding to Cart\r\n\r\nOnce an item is added to the cart, the system shall provide immediate feedback, such as a confirmation message or an update to the cart icon, to confirm to the user that the action was successful.\r\n5. Product Description\r\nFR10: Detailed Product Description\r\n\r\nThe product page shall include a detailed description that gives users essential information about the product. This description should be easily accessible and formatted for readability.\r\n6. Navigation and Bread Crumbs\r\nFR11: Breadcrumb Navigation\r\n\r\nThe product page shall include a breadcrumb trail that reflects the user's navigation path. This trail shall provide links that enable the user to go back to any previous category or directly to the home page.\r\nFR12: Breadcrumb Interactivity\r\n\r\nBreadcrumbs shall be interactive, allowing users to click on any part of the navigation path to return to that particular page or section.\r\n7. Responsive Design and Performance\r\nFR13: Responsive Design Consistency\r\n\r\nThe design of the product page must be responsive, automatically adjusting to the screen size of the device being used, and maintain functional and design consistency across various devices and browsers.\r\nFR14: Page Load Performance\r\n\r\nThe product page shall be optimized for performance, ensuring that content loads swiftly to minimize wait times and enhance the overall user experience.\r\n8. Error Handling and Validations\r\nFR15: Graceful Error Handling\r\n\r\nIn the event of an error, such as a failed addition to the cart due to stock limitations, the system shall provide a clear and informative message to the user, explaining the reason for the error and suggesting possible next steps.\r\nFR16: Validation of Attribute Selection\r\n\r\nBefore allowing the user to add a product to the cart, the system shall validate that all required attribute selections (size, color, etc.) have been made, preventing errors in the order process and ensuring the user's choices are available and valid.<br></div>
